The defendant Laura Susan Ziebell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Negligent Handling of Burning Material, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.10(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

3:19 PM Defendant Laura Susan Ziebell in court.  Attorney Richard S Gondik Jr in court for Laura Susan Ziebell.  Attorney Chad C La Lor in court for State of Wisconsin. Judge Anderson appears via video conference. Parties are agreeable to Judge appearing via zoom. Court calls case. State indicates will amend to negligent handling of burning materials pursuant to 941.10(1), joint recommendation of 90 days stayed for 1 year probation, conditions of DOC programming, 2 days conditional jail, 2 days credit, restitution of $3,781.11 to Auto Owners, costs plus surcharges.
Court recounts charges and possible penalties. Defendant pleads no contest. Court informs defendant of rights given up by their plea. Attorney stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made. Court finds Defendant understands all the rights they are waiving by their plea. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is entered.
State makes statements regarding prior offenses. State believes this is an appropriate resolution and asks court to adopt joint recommendation.
Attorney Gondik makes statements. Asks court to accept joint agreement.
Court orders count 1 90 days, imposed and stayed for 1 year probation,conditions of DOC programming, 2 days jail, 2 credit, time served. 3781.11 in restitution to Auto Owners, statutory court costs.
